25. Understanding Workplace Harassment with ADP 

Workplace harassment is an issue that is unfortunately common in many organizations. It can take many forms, including verbal, physical, or sexual harassment, and is never acceptable in any workplace. As an employee of a company whose payroll is managed by ADP, you should feel safe and protected from any form of harassment in your workplace. 

At ADP, we take workplace harassment seriously and have strict policies and procedures in place to prevent and address any incidents. Our policies are designed to create a safe and respectful workplace for all employees. These policies cover harassment, discrimination, and retaliation and are communicated to all employees during onboarding and through regular training sessions.

It is important to understand that harassment can take many forms, including unwelcome advances, inappropriate jokes, racial slurs or derogatory remarks, physical assault, and more. All of these behaviours are unacceptable and can create a hostile working environment for employees.

If you believe you have experienced or witnessed workplace harassment, we encourage you to speak up and report it to your supervisor or HR representative. ADP has a strict policy against retaliation, meaning that no employee will face any negative consequences for reporting harassment. 

In conclusion, as an employee of a company whose payroll is managed by ADP, it is important to understand workplace harassment and feel safe reporting incidents if they occur. ADP is committed to creating a safe and respectful workplace for all employees and has strict policies and procedures in place to prevent and address any incidents.